body:
@ldwnt while your analysis on the inner map makes sense to me, I have a couple of questions. 

- shouldn't `DecoderResolver` only be used by reader (not writer)?
- I assume you confirmed the memory issue from a heap dump?

>  I'd like to set up a small scale Data Lakehouse with Iceberg and DuckDB but I don't want to go near a JVM

@snth I'd like to see what's the scenario that you want to access iceberg table by non-jvm tools (if you don't mind). 

I agree that it's great thing to support iceberg in rust or other native languages.   From the current discussion, I see [risingwave](https://github.com/risingwavelabs/risingwave) and [starrocks](https://github.com/StarRocks/starrocks)  are requiring to integrate into iceberg datalake so they would be very happy to see the rust support.
